N. mitis

is used in TM practice in many African countries to treat conditions such as; syphilis, dysmenorrhea, scabies, rashes, female frigidity, and diarrhea. (

; 

; 

). Phytochemical and biological studies on this plant have been reported by many groups. Individual phytochemicals and crude extracts have been shown to have cytotoxicity (

), acaricidal, insecticidal (

), larvicidal, mosquitocidal (

